NOYS.preferred_label: acoustic noise in the water column

CAPH.definition: Measurements of air pressure as the dependent variable (ie excluding air pressure measured to specify the z co-ordinate of a balloon or sonde), including derived parameters such as tendency (rate of change) and related parameters such as air density.

CDTA.definition: Parameters quantifying the degree of hotness of the atmosphere. Specifically excludes indirect measurements of other parameters such as wet bulb temperatures.

ALKY.preferred_label: alkalinity acidity and ph of the water column
ALKY.definition: Parameters quantifying the hydrogen ion concentration in water bodies

HAAC.definition: Parameters quantifying the amount of organic compounds containing both a carboxyl group and an amino group in unlithified seabed material.

AMON.preferred_label: ammonium and ammonia concentration parameters in water bodies
AMON.definition: Ammonium and ammonia concentration parameters (including statistical parameters such as standard deviation) in any body of fresh or salt water.

BNUC.definition: Any enumeration of bacteria (Kingdom Monera so includes cyanobacteria) designated by terms other than taxonomic names (e.g. total) in any soil or sediment.

BNTX.preferred_label: bacteria generic abundance in water bodies
BNTX.definition: Any enumeration of bacteria (Kingdom Monera so includes cyanobacteria) designated by terms other than taxonomic names (e.g. total) in any body of fresh or salt water.

CBCC.definition: Parameters describing the size, shape or physiological activity of bacteria, defined as Kingdom Monera (includes cyanobacteria). Includes parameters both parameters mapped to taxa and those mapped to non-taxonomic groupings.

BNTC.preferred_label: bacteria non taxonomy-related biomass expressed as carbon per unit volume of the water column
BNTC.definition: Basically any bacteria carbon biomass parameters that aren't included in parameter group BATC because they cannot be mapped to specific taxa in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS. Bacteria are defined as Kingdom Monera, which includes cyanobacteria.

BATX.preferred_label: bacteria taxonomic abundance in water bodies
BATX.definition: Any enumeration of bacteria (Kingdom Monera so includes cyanobacteria) designated by taxonomic names (e.g. species, genus, family) in any body of fresh or salt water.

BATC.preferred_label: bacteria taxonomy-related biomass expressed as carbon per unit volume of the water column
BATC.definition: Bacteria carbon biomass parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS. These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards. Bacteria are defined as all taxa that fall into Kingdom Monera in the ITIS taxonomy, which includes cyanobacteria.

TBGZ.preferred_label: bacterial consumption in the water column

MBAN.definition: Depth of the water column or elevation of land surface relative to sea surface, geoid or other datum

LIBI.definition: Lipids are defined as small water-insoluble biomolecules including fats, fatty acids, esters, sterols, isoprenoid compounds, etc.. Biota includes any type of sample originating from a living organism.

GP088.definition: Parameters describing the actions or reactions of birds (Class Aves), usually in response to the environment. Includes both parameters mapped to taxa and those mapped to non-taxonomic groupings.

BRDA.definition: Parameters quantifying the number of birds (Class Aves) in a survey but not expressed per unit area. Includes presence/absence indicators.

GP004.definition: Parameters related to the reproduction of birds (Class Aves)

BRDD.preferred_label: bird taxonomy-related abundance per unit area of surface
BRDD.definition: Bird (Class Aves) abundance per unit area (of land or sea) presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS.These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards.

CBSD.definition: Concentrations of total, organic and inorganic carbon per unit weight of sediment. Sediment is understood to be the solid phase of the bed, including the recently settled material sometimes known as fluff collected from the bed surface.

CBSP.preferred_label: carbon concentrations in suspended particulate material
CBSP.definition: Concentrations of total, organic and inorganic carbon per unit weight of suspended particulate material collected by water column filtration, centrifugation or sediment trapping.

CETA.definition: Parameters that specify the number of specified members of Order Cetacea present at a particular time and location, including presence/absence indicators.

CEBH.definition: Parameters describing the actions or reactions of cetaceans (Order Cetacea), usually in response to the environment. Includes both parameters mapped to taxa and those mapped to non-taxonomic groupings.

CEMP.definition: Parameters describing the size, shape or physiological activity including disease and parasite infection status of cetaceans (Order Cetacea). Includes both parameters mapped to taxa and those mapped to non-taxonomic groupings.

CEMO.definition: Parameters describing the causes and rate of mortality in cetaceans (Order Cetacea). Includes both parameters mapped to taxa and those mapped to non-taxonomic groupings.

GP018.definition: Parameters related to the reproduction of cetaceans (Order Cetacea)

CPWC.definition: Includes all variants of chlorophyll expressed in terms of per unit volume, per unit area of any body of fresh or salt water, or as a relative colour index (e.g. PCI). Does not include data expressed per unit mass of SPM.

EPC00105.definition: Concentration of the pigment chlorophyll-a contained in the particulate material of a specified volume of any body of salt or fresh water.

EPC00106.definition: Concentration of the pigment chlorophyll-b contained in the particulate material of a specified volume of any body of salt or fresh water.

EPC00107.definition: Concentration of the pigment chlorophyll-c contained in the particulate material of a specified volume of any body of salt or fresh water.

COGE.definition: All parameters associated with coastal landforms such as beaches and dunes including morphology, evolution and associated transport phenomena

MTWC.preferred_label: colloidal metal concentrations in the water column
MTWC.definition: Concentrations of metal elements in the colloidal phase of the water column. Usually the dissolved concentration difference between conventionally filtered water and ultra-filtered water.

TOCH.preferred_label: concentration of carbohydrates, phenols, alkanols (alcohols), aldehydes and ketones in water bodies
TOCH.definition: Concentrations of carbohydrates, phenols, alkanols (alcohols), aldehydes and simple (non-alkenone) ketones in all phases of any body of fresh or salt water

TRIS.preferred_label: concentration of inorganic sulphur species in sediment
TRIS.definition: Concentration parameters for inorganic sulphur species in sediment (anything collected by a corer including fluff)

AAMN.preferred_label: concentration of nitrogen species in the atmosphere
AAMN.definition: Concentrations of both organic (eg amines) and inorganic (eg ammonia and oxides of nitrogen) nitrogen species in all phases of the atmosphere

STOM.preferred_label: concentration of organic matter in sediments
STOM.definition: Parameters quantifying the proportion of organic material in a soil or sediment sample

HMSB.preferred_label: concentration of organic matter in water bodies
HMSB.definition: Concentration (not 380nm light absorption) parameters for dissolved or total organic matter (includes humics, yellow matter, Gelbstoff) in any body of salt or fresh water.

OHWC.preferred_label: concentration of other hydrocarbons in the water column
OHWC.definition: 'Other' (not alkanes, alkenes, alkynes or PAHs) hydrocarbon concentration parameters (including saturation of gaseous species) in all phases of the water column. Does not include parameters expressed per unit weight of SPM.

BCOC.preferred_label: concentration of other organic contaminants in biota
BCOC.definition: Concentration parameters for carbon compounds regarded as environmentally harmful in either whole organisms or their constituent parts that are not included in other categories

SCOC.preferred_label: concentration of other organic contaminants in sediment samples
SCOC.definition: Concentration parameters for carbon compounds regarded as environmentally harmful in sediment, which is considered to be anything from the bed sampled by a grab or corer, including 'fluff' that are not included in other specific categories

PCOC.preferred_label: concentration of other organic contaminants in suspended particulate material
PCOC.definition: 'Other' organic contaminant (substances regarded as harmful other than PCBs and PAHs) concentrations in suspended particulate material, regarded as anything sampled by a water bottle, SAP, sediment trap etc. This group is for SPM composition measurements (concentration per unit weight) and NOT concentrations per unit volume of the water column in the particulate phase.

WCOC.preferred_label: concentration of other organic contaminants in the water column
WCOC.definition: Concentration parameters for carbon compounds regarded as environmentally harmful in solution or suspension (i.e.includes measurements in both the dissolved and particulate phases) in any body of salt or fresh water that are not included in other specific categories

BCOS.preferred_label: concentration of other substances in biota
BCOS.definition: 'Other' (than metals or organic contaminants) substance concentrations in either whole organisms or their constituent parts. This is a 'bucket' grouping that may be reclassified as the dictionary developes.

PTOX.definition: Parameters associated with the concentration of algae-generated toxins in either whole organisms or their constituent parts

BCPB.definition: PCB concentrations in either whole organisms or their constituent parts

SPCB.preferred_label: concentration of polychlorobiphenyls (pcbs) in sediment samples
SPCB.definition: PCB concentrations in sediment, which is considered to be anything from the bed sampled by a grab or corer, including 'fluff'

GP048.preferred_label: concentration of polychlorobiphenyls (pcbs) in the atmosphere
GP048.definition: Parameters quantifying polychlorobiphenyl (PCB) concentrations in all phases of the atmosphere

PPWC.preferred_label: concentration of polychlorobiphenyls (pcbs) in the water column
PPWC.definition: PCB concentrations in all phases of the water column. This group excludes SPM composition measurements (concentration per unit weight).

BCAH.preferred_label: concentration of polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons (pahs) in biota
BCAH.definition: PAH concentrations in either whole organisms or their constituent parts

SCAH.preferred_label: concentration of polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons (pahs) in sediment samples
SCAH.definition: PAH concentrations in sediment, which is considered to be anything from the bed sampled by a grab or corer, including 'fluff'

PCAH.preferred_label: concentration of polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons (pahs) in suspended particulate material
PCAH.definition: PAH concentrations in suspended particulate material, regarded as anything sampled by a water bottle, SAP, sediment trap etc. This group is for SPM composition measurements (concentration per unit weight) and NOT concentrations per unit volume of the water column in the particulate phase.

GP050.preferred_label: concentration of polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons (pahs) in the atmosphere
GP050.definition: Parameters quantifying polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon (PAH) concentrations in all phases of the atmosphere

PCHW.preferred_label: concentration of polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons (pahs) in the water column
PCHW.definition: PAH concentrations in all phases of the water column. This group includes concentrations per unit volume of the water column in the particulate phase, but not concentrations per unit wieght of SPM.

DPEV.definition: Parameters characterising the environment in which sediments were deposited either by observation or interpretation of sedimentary rocks and unlithified sediments.

OGPW.preferred_label: dissolved concentration parameters for other gases in sediment pore waters
OGPW.definition: All concentration parameters for inorganic dissolved gases other than oxygen and the noble gases in sediment pore water samples

SCOX.preferred_label: dissolved concentration parameters for other gases in the water column
SCOX.definition: All concentration parameters for inorganic dissolved gases other than oxygen and the noble gases in the water column

TDIN.preferred_label: dissolved inorganic nitrogen concentration in the water column
TDIN.definition: Total concentration of all dissolved inorganic nitrogen species in the water column, usually derived by summation of individual nutrient concentrations (NO3+NO2+NH4). Some workers may also include urea.

MTWD.definition: Concentrations of metal elements in the dissolved phase of the water column. This may include a contribution from the particulate phase if this has not been totally removed by filtration and the metal in question is reactive (ie detected as if it were dissolved) to the analytical technique used.

DOCC.preferred_label: dissolved organic carbon concentration in the water column
DOCC.definition: DOC per unit volume of the water column. Note that this includes some parameters that are strictly defined as total carbon, because the water was unfiltered on the assumption that POC was negligible.

OCPW.preferred_label: dissolved organic carbon concentrations in sediment pore waters
OCPW.definition: Concentrations of dissolved organic carbon in sediment pore waters

DOCU.preferred_label: dissolved organic carbon uptake and production in the water column
DOCU.definition: Any parameter relating to the rate of DOC concentration change in the water column

DOXY.preferred_label: dissolved oxygen parameters in the water column
DOXY.definition: All dissolved oxygen parameters (including saturation and utilisation) for the water column

TDNT.preferred_label: dissolved total and organic nitrogen concentrations in the water column
TDNT.definition: Concentration of total (organic plus inorganic) or organic dissolved nitrogen per unit volume of the water column. Grouped together as organic nitrogen frequently determined as total nitrogen.

TDPX.preferred_label: dissolved total or organic phosphorus concentration in the water column
TDPX.definition: Concentration of total (organic plus inorganic) or organic dissolved phosphorus per unit volume of the water column. Grouped together as organic phosphorus frequently determined as total phosphorus.

CNDC.preferred_label: electrical conductivity of the water column
CNDC.definition: Parameters quantifying the flow of electrical current through or the electrical resistance of a body of water at any point between the bed and the atmosphere

EXCR.preferred_label: excretion rate parameters in the water column
EXCR.definition: Includes all parameters relating to all mechanisms of waste release except respiration.

EXSV.definition: Measurements made at a given time of any state variable in a sample that is the subject of an experiment that will change the composition over time, such as the water sample in an incubation experiment.

FABD.preferred_label: fauna abundance per unit area of the bed
FABD.definition: Any fauna (class Animalia) abundance per unit are of sea, river or lake bed. Broad group overlapping a number of more specific groups that should be used preferentially, but this group is provided as an alternative to one-to-many mappings.

FATX.definition: Parameters that quantify the numbers of fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chrondrichthyes) at a given location in any body of salt or fresh water.

GP085.definition: Parameters describing the actions or reactions of fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chondrichthyes), usually in response to the environment. Includes both parameters mapped to taxa and those mapped to non-taxonomic groupings.

FIBM.definition: Parameters quantifying the mass of fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chrondrichthyes)in total or by species per unit area or per unit volume in any body of fresh or salt water expressed in any form (e.g. wet weight, dry weight, carbon, nitrogen, etc.).

GP005.definition: Parameters related to the infection of Fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chrondrichthyes) by parasites and disease. Includes visual assesements and analytical data.

FREP.definition: Parameters describing the extent, intensity, timing and method of reproduction in fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chrondrichthyes) including fecundity, reproductive rates, spawning, and nursery grounds.

FBAB.preferred_label: fish taxonomy-related abundance per unit area of the bed
FBAB.definition: Fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chondrichthyes) abundance per unit area of bed (sea, river, lake etc.) parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS. Includes animals normally considered as planktonic if they have been returned from sediment samples.

FBAF.preferred_label: fish taxonomy-related ash-free dry weight biomass per unit area of the bed
FBAF.definition: Fish (Osteichthyes, Agnatha and Chondrichthyes) ash-free dry weight biomass per unit area of bed (sea, river, lake etc.) parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS. Includes animals normally considered as planktonic if they have been returned from sediment samples.

GP087.definition: Parameters describing the extent, intensity, timing and method of fisheries

FEFF.definition: Parameters that quantify or classify the physical or financial resources used in fishing activities

RMAJ.preferred_label: geological sample major element chemistry deprecated
RMAJ.definition: Concentrations of the elements classically regarded as major (>1% by weight as oxide: namely: Si, Ti, Al, Fe3+, Fe2+, Mg, Mn, Ca, Na, and K) plus affiliated parameters such as H2O- (adsorbed water) and H2O+ (or loss on ignition) in rocks or sediments.

SRAD.definition: Any parameters quantifying ionising radiation emitted by cores or samples comprising rock, sediment (including surface sediment such as fluff)

GTCH.definition: Parameters quantifying the properties of rocks and sediments that are relevance to engineering such as physical strength and load-bearing capacity. Includes the disciplines of rock mechanics and soil mechanics.

GWAM.definition: Parameters quantifying the amount of groundwater in a given system such as aquifer water level and rate of flow of water through rock formations.

HBCH.definition: Parameters specifying the physical or chemical environment of a place where an organism is found.

HBEX.definition: Parameters specifying the vertical and horizontal spatial extent of the ecological character of a place where an organism is found

HFLX.preferred_label: heat fluxes between the water column and the atmosphere
HFLX.definition: Parameters quantifying heat exchange between any body of water and the atmosphere

ALAT.definition: All forms of horizontal spatial coordinates such as lat/lon and grid references

RFVL.preferred_label: horizontal velocity of the water column (currents)
RFVL.definition: Parameters expressing the velocity (including scalar speeds and directions) of water column horizontal movement, commonly termed Eulerian currents

ICEM.definition: Parameters specifying the speed and direction of sea or land ice and the stresses associated with this motion.

RMIN.preferred_label: inorganic chemical composition of sediment or rocks
RMIN.definition: Parameters specifying the proportions of inorganic components (major/minor/trace elements, trace metals etc.) in sediment or rock samples. Major elements includes the H2O+ and H2O- parameters reported by convention in oxide weight per cent geochemical major element analyses.

SPWC.definition: Concentration parameters (including saturation if gaseous) for inorganic sulphur species in all phases of the water column

INVD.definition: Parameters used to characterize and monitor biological invasion by non-native organisms.

LGCR.preferred_label: lagrangian currents and transport rates in the water column
LGCR.definition: Parameters expressing the mean nett transport rates within the water column like Lagrangian currents. Note this is an unintentional duplicate of VDFC.

LVEG.definition: Parameters relating to land (including marshes and the intertidal zone) vegetation

PPAB.preferred_label: light absorption in the water column

EXCO.definition: Parameters relating to the extent of light penetration into the water column

LITH.definition: Parameters describing rocks on the basis of physical characteristics such as colour, structure, mineralogy and grain size

GP012.preferred_label: macroalgae and seagrass infection and damage
GP012.definition: Parameters relating to diseases and parasites of macroalgae (Rhodophycota, Chromphycota, Chlorophycota) and seagrass (Charophyta, Anthophyta) and damage to seagrass beds

PU02.preferred_label: macroalgae generic abundance in water bodies
PU02.definition: Any enumeration (e.g. count, number per litre) of macroalgae (seaweeds) designated by terms other than taxonomic names (e.g. total) in any fresh or salt water body.

BCMT.definition: Metal concentrations in either whole organisms or their constituent parts.

MTSD.definition: Concentrations of metal elements per unit weight of sediment. Sediment is understood to be the solid phase of the bed, including the recently settled material sometimes known as fluff collected from the bed surface.

MTPW.preferred_label: metal concentrations in sediment pore waters
MTPW.definition: Concentrations of metal elements in sediment pore waters

MTSP.preferred_label: metal concentrations in suspended particulate material deprecated
MTSP.definition: Concentrations of metal elements in suspended particulate material collected by water column filtration, centrifugation or sediment trapping. Deprecated as semantic overlap with MTWP.

MTAT.definition: Concentration of metal elements in any phase of the atmosphere

HVYMTL.definition: Concentrations of metals and metalloids, some of which are of environmental concern. This category also includes selenium (Se), a reactive non-metal, but excludes silicon (Si, a metalloid) as this is mapped to the P36 SLCATE.

UMLS.definition: Parameters describing the abundance and nature of microscopic particles of man-made materials and in particular microplastics present in the sediment.

UMLW.definition: Parameters describing the abundance and nature of microscopic particles of man-made materials and in particular microplastics present in any body of fresh or salt water.

MZBN.preferred_label: microzooplankton generic abundance in water bodies
MZBN.definition: Any enumeration (e.g. count, number per litre) of microzooplankton (free swimming heterotrophic organisms smaller than 200um) designated by terms other than taxonomic names (e.g. total) in any fresh or salt water body.

MZCT.definition: Parameters that express the consumption of the phytoplankton population by the microzooplankton. Generally the results of dilution experiments on water samples screened through a 200-micron mesh.

MATX.preferred_label: microzooplankton taxonomic abundance in water bodies
MATX.definition: Any enumeration (e.g. count, number per litre) of microzooplankton (free swimming heterotrophic organisms smaller than 200um) designated by taxonomic names (e.g. species, genus or family) in any fresh or salt water body.

MATC.preferred_label: microzooplankton taxonomy-related biomass expressed as carbon per unit volume of the water column
MATC.definition: Microzooplankton carbon biomass parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS. These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards., but exclude morphological classifications such as 'heterotrophic flagellate'.

MPMN.definition: Parameters expressing depth (possibly as pressure) of an instrument on a suspended underwater mooring. These are primarily collected to monitor mooring performance by quantifying knock-down and should not be regarded as instrument z co-ordinates (accurate calibration is rare) or as sea level measurements.

NTRA.preferred_label: nitrate concentration parameters in the water column
NTRA.definition: Nitrate concentration parameters (including statistical parameters such as standard deviation) in the water column. Includes nitrate+nitrite, which is often loosely referred to as nitrate.

NTRZ.preferred_label: nitrate+nitrite concentration parameters in the water column deprecated
NTRZ.definition: Deprecated term from a misguided attempt to distinguish between NO3 and NO3+NO2 for discovery. Use parameter group NTRA instead

NTRI.preferred_label: nitrite concentration parameters in the water column
NTRI.definition: Nitrite concentration parameters (including statistical parameters such as standard deviation) in the water column

NTSD.definition: Concentrations of total, organic and inorganic nitrogen per unit weight of sediment. Sediment is understood to be the solid phase of the bed, including the recently settled material sometimes known as fluff collected from the bed surface.

R410.preferred_label: ocean colour and earth-leaving visible waveband spectral radiation
R410.definition: Parameters associated with the measurement of ocean colour, including visible waveband satellite spectral radiometer measurements, their calibration measurements (spectral water-leaving radiance and reflectance) and chart colour estimates.

OPBS.definition: Includes all parameters covering the strength of electromagnetic radiation signal return, including absolute measurements of returning signal strength as well as parameters expressed as backscatter (the proportion of transmitted signal returned)

OMPW.preferred_label: organometallic and organometalloid species concentration parameters in sediments
OMPW.definition: All organometallic and orgamometalloid compound concentration parameters (including saturations for gaseous species) in all phases of sediments (including pore waters)

OMBI.preferred_label: organometallic species concentration parameters in biota
OMBI.definition: All measurements of the quantity or mass of any organometallic compound in any living organisms or their component parts

CING.preferred_label: particulate inorganic carbon concentrations in the water column
CING.definition: Concentrations of inorganic carbon in the particulate phase of the water column as extracted by a fitration technique. This is the particle-bound concentration per unit volume of the water column. Consequently, it is both a function of the SPM concentration in the water column and the concentration of inorganic carbon per unit weight of the SPM.

MTWP.preferred_label: particulate metal concentrations in the water column
MTWP.definition: Concentration parameters for metallic elements in the particulate phase of the water column collected by fitration, centrifugation or sediment trapping

CORG.preferred_label: particulate total and organic carbon concentrations in the water column
CORG.definition: Concentrations of total and organic carbon in the particulate phase of the water column as extracted by a filtration technique. This is the particle-bound concentration per unit volume of the water column and is both a function of the SPM concentration in the water column and the concentration of carbon per unit weight of SPM. Total and organic carbon are classed together to circumvent confusion caused by total carbon data sets labelled 'POC' on the assumption that the inorganic carbon fraction is negligible

NTOT.preferred_label: particulate total and organic nitrogen concentrations in the water column
NTOT.definition: Concentrations of total and organic nitrogen in the particulate phase of the water column, which is a function of both the SPM concentration in the water column and the concentration of nitrogen per unit weight of SPM. Note that it is commonly assumed that all particulate nitrogen is organic.

EPC00133.definition: The partial pressure of carbon dioxide gas in an atmosphere that is in equilibrium with a sample from any body of fresh or salt water.

PEBI.definition: Concentration parameters for substances synthesised by man to kill other life forms in either whole organisms or their constituent parts.

PESD.definition: Concentration parameters for substances synthesised by man to kill other life forms in sediment, which is considered to be anything from the bed sampled by a grab or corer, including 'fluff'.

PESP.preferred_label: pesticide concentrations in suspended particulate material
PESP.definition: Concentration parameters for substances synthesised by man to kill other life forms in suspended particulate material (SPM) collected by water column filtration, centrifugation or sediment trapping. Only includes parameters expressed per unit mass of SPM and not per unit volume of the water column.

PEWB.definition: Concentration parameters for substances synthesised by man to kill other life forms in either solution or suspension (i.e.includes measurements in both the dissolved and particulate phases) in any body of salt or fresh water.

PHWC.preferred_label: phaeopigment concentrations in the water column
PHWC.definition: Includes all variants of phaeopigment (chlorophyll degradation products) expressed in terms of per unit volume or unit area of the water column. Does not include data expressed per unit mass of SPM.

PHOS.preferred_label: phosphate concentration parameters in the water column
PHOS.definition: Phosphate concentration parameters (including statistical parameters such as standard deviation) in the water column

PHYC.preferred_label: phycobolin pigment concentrations in the water column
PHYC.definition: Concentration of phycobolin group pigments such as phycocyanin and phycoerythrin in the water column

PNTX.preferred_label: phytoplankton generic abundance in water bodies
PNTX.definition: Any enumeration (e.g. count, abundance) of free-floating autotrophic biological entities designated by terms other than taxonomic names (e.g. microphytoplankton, ciliate, flagellate) in any body of fresh or salt water.

CNTX.preferred_label: phytoplankton generic biomass in water bodies
CNTX.definition: Any parameterisation of biomass (e.g. wet weight, dry weight, carbon, nitrogen etc.) of free-floating autotrophic biological entities designated by terms other than taxonomic names (e.g. microphytoplankton, ciliate, flagellate) in any body of fresh or salt water.

PATX.preferred_label: phytoplankton taxonomic abundance in water bodies
PATX.definition: Any enumeration (e.g. count, abundance) of free-floating autotrophic biological entities designated by taxonomic names (e.g. species, genus, family) in any body of fresh or salt water.

CATX.preferred_label: phytoplankton taxonomic biomass in water bodies
CATX.definition: Any parameterisation of biomass (e.g. wet weight, dry weight, carbon, nitrogen etc.) of free-floating autotrophic biological entities identified by their taxonomic names (e.g. family, genus, species) in any body of fresh or salt water.

PYTT.preferred_label: plankton abundance per unit volume of the water column
PYTT.definition: Used for plankton abundance parameters where no differentiation between phytoplankton, microzooplankton or zooplankton is possible

CYEU.preferred_label: plankton biomass expressed as carbon per unit volume of the water column
CYEU.definition: Used for plankton carbon biomass parameters where no differentiation between phytoplankton, microzooplankton or zooplankton is possible

PPRD.preferred_label: primary production in the water column
PPRD.definition: Parameters associated with the quantification of primary production. This is defined as the fixation of carbon dioxide into either organic or inorganic carbon by living entities and so includes photosynthesis and calcification.

RBSC.definition: Includes all parameters covering the strength of emitted microwave radiation return, including absolute measurements of returning signal strength as well as parameters expressed as backscatter (the proportion of transmitted signal returned)

BRAD.definition: All parameters associated with radioactivity in either whole organisms or their constituent parts

WRAD.definition: All parameters associated with radioactivity in any body of fresh or salt water, including radiation counts, isotope activities and activity ratios. Activities per unit mass of SPM are included.

OXYC.definition: Raw parameters (usually membrane current and temperature) from dissolved oxygen sensors

PHLT.definition: Raw pH parameter output from any type of pH sensor.

TCNT.preferred_label: raw temperature and/or salinity instrument output
TCNT.definition: Direct output parameters from TS instruments such as thermosalinograph or CTD

EPSV.definition: Raw direct output parameters from microstructure sensors, probes or profilers that are used to determine the distribution of water body properties on a millimetric scale.

PSAL.definition: Parameters quantifying the concentration of sodium chloride in any body of water at any point between the bed and the atmosphere

SAMP.definition: Qualitative and quantitative parameters related to the sampling activity; includes terms related to sampling effort, sampling gears, sample processing.

ASLV.definition: Measurements and predictions of the displacement of the water column surface from a fixed, stable reference

SBGE.definition: Parameters associated with seafloor landforms and features such as bedforms, seamounts and ridges, including morphology, evolution and associated transport phenomena.

BPRP.definition: Parameters that quantify any attribute of a biological entity specified elsewhere in the data model and therefore do not map to the existing biologically classified P02 categories. This concept is used as a temporary grouping of parameter codes created for the SeaDataNet biological standard format.

SLIT.definition: Parameters describing the abundance and nature of litter data collected on the seabed.

FOCA.definition: Parameters related to the distribution of true seals (Phocidae), eared seals (Otariidae) and walruses (Odobenidae)at a particular time and location, including presence/absence indicators.

SEBH.definition: Parameters describing the actions or reactions, usually in response to the environment, of true seals (Phocidae), eared seals (Otariidae) and walruses (Odobenidae).

SEMP.definition: Parameters describing the size, shape or physiological activity including disease and parasite infection status of true seals (Phocidae), eared seals (Otariidae) and walruses (Odobenidae).

SEMO.definition: Parameters describing the causes and rate of mortality of true seals (Phocidae), eared seals (Otariidae) and walruses (Odobenidae).

GP025.definition: Parameters related to the reproduction of true seals (Phocidae), eared seals (Otariidae) and walruses (Odobenidae).

SECC.definition: Measurements of optical visibility in the water column

RACC.definition: Parameters quantifying the volume, mass or thickness of particulate material that gathers on the seabed per unit time.

SDAC.definition: Parameters relating to the elucidation of sediment structure by quantifying the proportion of waves from a low energy source reflected by sub-surface layers.

MNGS.definition: Parameters specifying the physical dimensions of the particles comprising unlithified sediment (including expressions of shape such as aspect ratio) and statistics derived from their variation in a sample (e.g. mean, mode, sorting, skewness).

GHDX.definition: Parameters relating to the size, shape and form of microfossils in sediment samples

BEST.definition: Parameters quantifying the critera for and extent of sediment resuspension

STCO.definition: Parameters that describe the degree to which unlithified sediment is able to conduct heat

WCWT.preferred_label: sediment water content, porosity and surface area
WCWT.definition: Sediment porosity (water content by volume) and water content by weight parameters

SSTR.definition: Parameters characterising structure in sedimentary rocks and unlithified sediment such as bedding, lamination and bioturbation.

FPFX.preferred_label: sedimentation flux of biological detritus in the water column
FPFX.definition: Flux of biological detritus (material derived from the water column such as exuvia and faecal pellets) in the water column

MSFX.preferred_label: sedimentation flux quantification in the water column
MSFX.definition: Parameters expressing the total sedimentation flux in terms of particle mass, volume or counts

SRFL.definition: Parameters relating to the elucidation of geological structure by quantifying the proportion of waves from a high energy source reflected by sub-surface layers.

SRFR.definition: Parameters relating to the elucidation of geological structure by quantifying the refration of waves from a high energy source by sub-surface layers.

SABB.preferred_label: shellfish abundance and biomass in water bodies
SABB.definition: Parameters that quantify the numbers or amount of living material of shellfish (molluscs - including cephalopods - and crustaceans of interest to fisheries research and commercial fisheries) in any body of fresh or salt water.

SATM.definition: Parameters that quantify the size, shape, age and life processes (including mortality) of shellfish (molluscs - including cephalopods - and crustaceans of interest to fisheries research and commercial fisheries).

SLCA.preferred_label: silicate concentration parameters in the water column
SLCA.definition: Silicate concentration parameters (including statistical parameters such as standard deviation) in the water column

SPCN.definition: Physical, chemical or optical properties of individual solid particles.

PSST.preferred_label: skin temperature of the water column
PSST.definition: Temperature of the water column surface as measured by a radiometer. It does NOT include temperature measurements in the upper few metres of the water column such as thermosalinograph data

CRYS.preferred_label: snow and ice mass, thickness and extent
CRYS.definition: Measurements of quantity (mass), thickness and spatial extent of snow and ice

IPHY.preferred_label: snow and ice physical properties and characteristics
IPHY.definition: Parameters related to physical properties (e.g. colour, density, in-situ temperature) or characteristics (e.g. sea ice type) of any kind of water sample that was in its solid state at the time of sampling or measurement

SPAG.definition: Measured or stratigraphically estimated ages of secondary mineral deposits in caves. This includes stalactites, stalagmites, flowstone, and crystal growths.

WSTB.definition: Stable isotope parameters (concentrations, ratios and enrichments) in both the dissolved and particulate phases of any body of fresh or salt water.

MXLM.preferred_label: structure and stability of the water column
MXLM.definition: Parameters describing or predicting water column structure plus parameters quantifying the dynamic stability of that structure

SPGS.preferred_label: suspended particulate material grain size parameters
SPGS.definition: Includes all SPM grain size measurements and derived statistics

TSED.preferred_label: suspended particulate material in the water column
TSED.definition: Parameters quantifying SPM concentration in the water column by weight, by volume or in terms of turbidity

TEMP.definition: Temperature parameters in any body of water at any point between the bed and the atmosphere excluding the top few microns sampled by radiometers known as the skin

TD00.preferred_label: terrestrial detritus in the water column suspended particulate material
TD00.definition: Parameters quantifying and categorising terrestrially-derived detritus (eg dust and pollen) in the water column

COAS.definition: Parameters relating to the mapping of terrestrial features, including coastlines

MTWT.preferred_label: total metal concentrations in water bodies
MTWT.definition: Concentration parameters for metal elements in the combined dissolved and particulate phases of any body of fresh or salt water.

MDSD.preferred_label: trace metalloid concentrations in sediment deprecated
MDSD.definition: Concentration parameters for metalloid elements in sediment. Sediment is understood to be the solid phase of the bed, including the recently settled material sometimes known as fluff collected from the bed surface. Metalloids are considered as B, Ge, As, Sb, Te and Po (but not Si which is classed separately because of its major role in environmental chemistry)

TRAN.definition: Parameters quantifying the level of activity moving people or cargo from one place to another.

VDFC.definition: Parameters describing the transport of material, heat or energy in the water column

EPSI.definition: Measured parameters expressing turbulence in the water column plus parameters derived from these measurements

EPC00010.definition: Concentration of urea per unit volume of a river, estuary, sea or ocean by any method in filtered or unfiltered water.

CMFL.definition: Parameters measured by variable fluorescence instruments such as pump and probe and fast repetition rate fluorometers

AHGT.definition: All vertical spatial parameters including depth, height and pressure when used as an independent variable.

LRZA.preferred_label: vertical velocity of the water column (currents)
LRZA.definition: Vertical water movement parameters including non-directional speeds

VIRU.definition: Any enumeration (e.g. count, number per square metre) of viruses in any body of fresh or salt water.

VSRW.preferred_label: visible waveband radiance and irradiance measurements in the water column
VSRW.definition: Includes measurements at discrete wavelengths and PAR integrated values, measurements as photon and energy fluxes.

WQBI.definition: Parameters quantifying fauna and flora that indicate physical or chemical conditions in the water column such as colonisation depths and abundance of indicator species.

WVST.definition: Statistical parameters derived from wave records to express wave height and period.

EWSB.definition: Parameters quantifying the extent or direction of atmospheric movement. Obvious examples are wind velocity, windspeed and wind direction, but can also include derived parameters such as force, energy, power and power density.

WSTR.definition: Parameters related to forces due to interactions between atmosphere and the surface of the earth or between atmospheric air masses

MFAB.definition: Any enumeration (e.g. count, number per square metre) of animals living on or near the seabed designated by terms other than taxonomic names (e.g. total).

ZBTX.definition: Any enumeration (e.g. count, number per square metre) of animals living on or near the seabed designated by taxonomic names (e.g. species, genus).

ZWTX.preferred_label: zoobenthos taxonomy-related wet weight biomass per unit area of the bed
ZWTX.definition: Zoobenthos wet weight biomass per unit area parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS. Includes animals considered as planktonic if they have been returned from sediment samples.

BLEN.definition: Morphological parameters of zooplankton and zoobenthos (essentially any animal except for insects, earthworms or fish), such as size, shape and weight. Benthic and planktonic animals have not been seggregated because there is a degree of overlap (eg shrimps).

ZFIT.preferred_label: zooplankton and zoobenthos physiological condition parameters
ZFIT.definition: Parameters indicating the health of zooplankton and zoobenthos taxa, such as fecundity, egg condition, presence of parasites/diseases etc.

ZCMP.definition: Chemical composition of zooplankton expressed in terms of mass (or molar quantity) per specimen or per unit tissue mass

ZNTX.preferred_label: zooplankton non taxonomy-related abundance per unit volume of the water column
ZNTX.definition: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton plus larger pelagic animals excluding fish, reptiles and mammals) abundance per unit volume parameters not included in group ZATX. Usually used for generic names such as 'mesozooplankton'.

ZNTC.preferred_label: zooplankton non taxonomy-related biomass expressed as carbon per unit volume of the water column
ZNTC.definition: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton plus larger pelagic animals excluding fish, reptiles and mammals) carbon biomass per unit volume parameters not included in group ZCTC. Usually used for generic names such as 'mesozooplankton'.

ZNTN.preferred_label: zooplankton non taxonomy-related biomass expressed as nitrogen per unit volume of the water column
ZNTN.definition: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton plus larger pelagic animals excluding fish, reptiles and mammals) nitrogen biomass per unit volume parameters not included in group ZCTC. Usually used for generic names such as 'mesozooplankton'.

ZATX.preferred_label: zooplankton taxonomy-related abundance per unit volume of the water column
ZATX.definition: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton plus larger pelagic animals excluding fish, reptiles and mammals) abundance parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS. These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards.

ZCTC.preferred_label: zooplankton taxonomy-related biomass expressed as carbon per unit volume of the water column
ZCTC.definition: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton plus larger pelagic animals excluding fish, reptiles and mammals) carbon biomass parameters presented at the level of taxa that may be mapped to entities in a standard taxonomy registry such as WoRMS or ITIS. These may be at any taxonomic level from sub-species upwards.

ZATP.preferred_label: zooplankton taxonomy-related biomass expressed as protein per unit volume of the water column
ZATP.definition: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton plus larger pelagic animals excluding fish, reptiles and mammals) protein biomass per unit volume for entities that have been identified by taxonomic name

GP079.definition: Zooplankton (mesozooplankton and larger, exclusing fish, mammals, reptiles and insects) biomass determined by weighing unprocessed catch samples.
